# Extract Pure Frontend from PEC App (Remove Firebase/Backend)

## Problem & Context

The PEC App project is a Vite + React + TypeScript campus ERP with **Firebase deeply embedded as the data layer and auth system across 68+ files**. Every page directly imports Firestore/Auth functions and makes inline CRUD calls. The goal is to rip out all Firebase, MongoDB, and backend dependencies to produce a **pure frontend shell** that can later connect to your Prisma/Postgres/Redis/Next.js backend.

> [!CAUTION]
> **This is a very large-scale refactoring task.** Firebase is not just used for auth — it IS the entire data layer. Every single page (Dashboard, Courses, Attendance, Finance, Placements, etc.) directly calls `getDocs`, `addDoc`, `updateDoc`, `deleteDoc` from Firestore inline. There is no abstraction/service layer in between. This means:
> - After removing Firebase, **all data-fetching and data-mutation logic in every page will be replaced with mock/placeholder data**
> - Pages will render with **static mock data** and the UI will be fully intact
> - You will need to later wire up your Next.js API routes in place of the mock data

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Key decision: What should replace Firebase data operations?**
> 
> Since Firebase is the ENTIRE data layer (not just auth), removing it means every page that fetches/writes data needs a replacement strategy. I propose:
> 
> 1. **Replace [config/firebase.ts](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/src/config/firebase.ts)** with a no-op module (exports empty stubs)
> 2. **Replace [hooks/useAuth.ts](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/src/hooks/useAuth.ts)** with a mock that returns a hardcoded demo user (so all pages render)
> 3. **Replace all Firestore calls in pages** with mock/static data so the UI renders identically
> 4. **Replace [OrganizationContext](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/src/contexts/OrganizationContext.tsx#7-12)** with a mock organization
> 5. **Remove** `firebase`, `firebase-admin`, `mongodb`, `mongoose` from [package.json](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/package.json)
> 6. **Delete** the `scripts/` folder (18 Firebase seed scripts) and [firestore.rules](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/firestore.rules)
> 
> The UI/components/styling will be 100% preserved. Only the data source changes from "live Firebase" to "static mock data."

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Config Layer

#### [MODIFY] [firebase.ts](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/src/config/firebase.ts)
Replace with a stub module that exports mock objects (`auth`, `db`, `storage`) so existing imports don't break. All Firebase SDK imports will be removed.

---

### 2. Auth Layer

#### [MODIFY] [useAuth.ts](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/src/hooks/useAuth.ts)
Replace Firebase Auth listener with a mock that returns a hardcoded demo user:
- `uid: 'demo-user'`
- `role: 'student'` (configurable)
- `isAuthenticated: true`
- `permissions`: full permissions object
- No Firebase imports at all

#### [MODIFY] [OrganizationContext.tsx](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/src/contexts/OrganizationContext.tsx)
Replace Firestore-based org fetching with mock organization data.

---

### 3. Components with Firebase

#### [MODIFY] [ProtectedRoute.tsx](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/src/components/ProtectedRoute.tsx)
Replace Firebase auth check with mock auth (always authenticated).

#### [MODIFY] [OrgScopeRedirect.tsx](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/src/components/OrgScopeRedirect.tsx)
Replace Firestore lookups with mock data.

#### [MODIFY] [Header.tsx](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/src/components/layout/Header.tsx)
Replace Firebase `signOut` with a no-op or redirect.

#### [MODIFY] [FacultyScheduleManager.tsx](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/src/components/timetable/FacultyScheduleManager.tsx)
Replace Firestore CRUD with mock data.

#### [MODIFY] Attendance components ([QRAttendanceScanner.tsx](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/src/components/attendance/QRAttendanceScanner.tsx), [QRAttendanceGenerator.tsx](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/src/components/attendance/QRAttendanceGenerator.tsx))
Replace Firestore calls with mock data.

---

### 4. All Pages (~50 files)

Every page in `src/pages/` that imports from `@/config/firebase` or `firebase/*` will be modified:
- Remove all `firebase/*` imports
- Remove all `@/config/firebase` imports
- Replace all `getDocs`/`getDoc`/`addDoc`/`updateDoc`/`deleteDoc`/`collection`/`query`/`where`/`onSnapshot` calls with mock/static data
- Preserve ALL UI rendering, components, styling, animations exactly as-is
- State management (`useState`, `useEffect`) will be preserved but load mock data

**Files affected (representative list):**
- Auth: `AuthEnhanced.tsx`, `Auth.tsx`, `RoleSelection.tsx`, `Onboarding.tsx`
- Core: `Dashboard.tsx`, `StudentProfile.tsx`, `Courses.tsx`, `Timetable.tsx`
- Finance: `Finance.tsx`, `PaymentDetail.tsx`
- Placements: `Jobs.tsx`, `PlacementDrives.tsx`, `PlacementApplications.tsx`, + 10 more
- College Admin: `Departments.tsx`, `Faculty.tsx`, `DepartmentDetail.tsx`
- Dashboards: All 7 role-based dashboards
- And ~20 more pages

---

### 5. Lib/Utils

#### [MODIFY] Service files in `src/lib/` that use Firebase
- `chatManagement.service.ts`, `chatRooms.service.ts`, `messages.service.ts` — Replace Firestore with mock data
- `accessControl.ts` — Remove Firebase auth checks

#### [MODIFY] [orgRouting.tsx](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/src/utils/orgRouting.tsx)
Replace Firestore lookups with mock data.

#### [DELETE] [seedPlacementData.ts](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/src/utils/seedPlacementData.ts)
Firebase-specific seeding utility.

---

### 6. Project Configuration

#### [MODIFY] [package.json](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/package.json)
Remove dependencies: `firebase`, `firebase-admin`, `mongodb`, `mongoose`
Remove scripts: `api`, `dev:all`, `db:init`

#### [DELETE] [firestore.rules](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/firestore.rules)
Firebase security rules — no longer needed.

#### [DELETE] All files in `scripts/` directory (18 Firebase seed scripts)

#### [MODIFY] [.env.example](file:///d:/PEC_APP/omnifow/.env.example)
Remove any Firebase-related env vars (currently none, but ensure cleanliness).

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run build` to verify the project compiles without errors after all changes
- Run `npm run lint` to check for any import/reference errors

### Manual Verification
1. Run `npm run dev` and open the app in browser
2. Verify landing page loads correctly with all styling/animations
3. Navigate to `/auth` — should show the auth page UI (login form visible, no Firebase errors in console)
4. Navigate to a dashboard route — should render with mock data
5. Check browser console for zero Firebase-related errors
6. Verify no `firebase` imports remain: `grep -r "firebase" src/`
